  "The magnet heats the screen": "",
  "The magnetic field deflects the electron beam, causing it to hit different phosphor dots": "",
  "In a CRT, electrons are steered by electromagnetic fields to hit specific phosphor dots. An external magnet deflects the beam (F = qv × B), causing electrons to hit wrong phosphors and distorting the colors.": "",
  "Two parallel wires carry current in the same direction. The wires will:": "",
  "Not interact magnetically": "",
  "Attract each other": "",
  "Repel each other": "",
  "Twist around each other": "",
  "Parallel currents in the same direction attract each other. Each wire's magnetic field exerts a force on the other wire directed toward it. This is the basis for defining the ampere.": "",
  "A particle accelerator uses a magnetic field of 1.5 T to bend protons (m = 1.67 × 10⁻²⁷ kg, q = 1.6 × 10⁻¹⁹ C) traveling at 2 × 10⁷ m/s into a circular path. What is the radius of the proton's path?": "",
